						<summary>

						<p>Broken slab set up in the temple of Abbaṇaśeṭṭi Gōpālakṛishṇadēva.</p>						

						<p>Circa 15th century.</p>						

						<p>This mutilated record registers gifts of lands etc. probably to god Kṛishṇadēva by several individuals. It refers to the two villages Keñjūru and Cherppaḷḷi and to Bemmaṇañcha Toḷaha. All other details are lost. </p>						

						</summary>
